      "stem_html": "<p>The following model is that of an aldopentose. Draw a Fischer projection of the sugar, name it, and identify it as a <small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small> sugar or an <small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">L</small> sugar.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbW9aIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--8e6897b6e3155187ae6d8f397371a8320b08e09a/OChem_25_04_005.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model of an aldopentose. It contains five carbon atoms, four hydroxyl groups, and one aldehyde group.\">",
